Gems/Premium Currency:
\f0\b0  A rarer currency (could be gems, diamonds, etc.) obtained from Gift Box Bosses or big treasure chests. These are used for special upgrades or cosmetic purchases \
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Gear and Equipment:
\f0\b0  The player can find weapons, armor, and trinkets that improve their combat ability. For example, a 
\f1\b Sword of Flames
\f0\b0  that adds burn damage on hit, or 
\f1\b Shadow Cloak
\f0\b0  armor that occasionally evades an attack. Gear can drop from bosses, elite enemies, or appear in chests. Each gear item has a rarity (common, rare, epic, legendary) which determines its power and drop rate. A 
\f3\i loot table
\f0\i0  controls what drops from where \'96 for instance, bosses have a high chance to drop at least rare or better gear. Gear provides the 
\f1\b primary means of increasing the hero\'92s stats
\f0\b0  during a run: better weapons = more damage, better armor = more survivability. This ties into progression because as you delve deeper, you\'92ll need stronger gear which you hopefully looted on the way.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Consumables/Power-ups:
\f0\b0  These are one-time use items that give short boosts or effects. For example, a 
\f1\b Healing Potion
\f0\b0  to restore HP, an 
\f1\b Invincibility Star
\f0\b0  that grants 3 seconds of invulnerability, or a 
\f1\b Bomb
\f0\b0  that clears nearby enemies. These can drop from random enemies or chests, and the player can store a limited number (or they auto-activate on pickup, depending on design). Power-ups add a classic arcade feel and can save the player in a pinch, complementing the core skills.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Gift Boxes:
\f0\b0  True to the theme, 
\f1\b Gift Box pickups
\f0\b0  will appear randomly in the dungeon. A gift box is like a mini-chest \'96 when collected or opened, it gives a surprise reward. For instance, a gift box might pop out of a destroyed object or spawn after clearing a wave. The contents are randomized: sometimes just coins, other times a piece of gear or a pet. The thrill of seeing a wrapped gift on the ground and opening it is a fun moment that reinforces the gift theme. We can even have different sizes/colors of gift boxes, with bigger ones yielding better loot.\
