\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Enemy Drops:
\f0\b0  Every enemy killed has a chance to drop something \'96 even if small. Common mobs mainly drop coins or occasional health pickups; elite mobs might drop a chest or gear. The drop logic can use increasing probability for better loot on tougher enemies.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Combo Rewards:
\f0\b0  If the player kills enemies in quick succession or completes a wave without taking damage, trigger a 
\f1\b \'93bonus gift\'94
\f0\b0  drop. For example, a multi-kill could spawn an extra gift box on the path or trigger a coin shower. This encourages skilled play and makes combat flashy. It\'92s an arcade sensibility: do well and the game literally rewards you mid-run.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Stage Completion:
\f0\b0  When a stage boss is defeated (and after any Gift Box Boss), reward the player with a 
\f1\b treasure chest
\f0\b0 . Opening this chest yields a bunch of coins and a guaranteed item (or two). This is effectively the \'93level up loot\'94. It feels like the boss guarded a treasure, which fits the dungeon theme.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 All these sources combined mean the player is frequently picking up something, be it currency or items, which maintains excitement. The 
\f1\b art and sound for loot
